CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1957, pg. A17 reads: "The FROGS sponsored one of the prettiest formals of the season Friday at the Gateway Plaza. During intermission they purchased a $500 life membership in NAACP.  Franklin Williams, director of the NAACP Freedom Fund, is shown presenting the club with a citation.  Roland Sawyer, president of the organiation [sic], is pictured left center in the back row, accepting the plaque from Mr. Williams."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of FROGS members, including Roland Sawyer, center left, back row, receiving NAACP citation on behalf of the FROGS from Franklin Williams, director of the NAACP Freedom Fund, with Morris Fountain Sr., second from left in front, and Dr. Reginald Dixon second from right in back, gathered in Gateway Plaza for formal
